background-phi-colors.enabled.descriptio: Enables that colors background. ( `Background Phi Colors: Mute` and` Background Phi Colors: Mute All` commands take precedence over this setting. )
background-phi-colors.enabledPanels.desc: Enables that colors background in output panels.

background-phi-colors.basicDelay.descrip: Delay from event occurrence to coloring. ( millisecond )

background-phi-colors.baseColor.descript: Background colors are automatically generated by rotating the hue by 1 / phi all around based on this color. ( #RRGGBB )
background-phi-colors.spaceBaseColor.des: Space background colors are automatically generated by rotating the hue by 1 / phi all around based on this color. If this value is null `background-phi-colors.baseColor` will be used instead. ( #RRGGBB )
background-phi-colors.symbolBaseColor.de: Symbol background colors are automatically generated by rotating the hue by 1 / phi all around based on this color. If this value is null `background-phi-colors.baseColor` will be used instead. ( #RRGGBB )
background-phi-colors.symbolColorMap.des: You can specify the background color for each symbol.
background-phi-colors.tokenBaseColor.des: Token background colors are automatically generated by rotating the hue by 1 / phi all around based on this color. If this value is null `background-phi-colors.baseColor` will be used instead. ( #RRGGBB )
background-phi-colors.tokenColorMap.desc: You can specify the background color for each token.
background-phi-colors.indentMode.descrip: `none`: does not color indents, `light`: colors all indents statically, `smart`: colors the current indent, `full`: light + smart
background-phi-colors.tokenMode.descript: `none`: does not color tokens, `light`: colors all tokens statically, `smart`:colors the tokens contained in the current line, `full`: light + smart
background-phi-colors.activeScope.descri: `editor`: each editor is highlighted independently, `document`: highlight are shared in the same document editors, `window`: highlight are shared in the all editors
